The paper deals with the synthesis of reactive systems from LTL specifications, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields of computer science. The use of parity games and automata-theoretic approaches suggests that the paper may belong to the logic (cs.LO) or programming languages (cs.PL) subcategories. Additionally, the paper discusses heuristics and data structures used in the implementation, which could indicate a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the comparison of techniques on benchmark sets suggests a potential connection to formal methods (cs.FL).
